# Lanza CMS — local dev secrets. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in:
#   cp .sample.env .env
#
# GitHub fine-grained PAT with Contents: read/write on the content repo.
# Used ONLY by the dev GitHub proxy in vite.config.ts (server-side); it is
# deliberately NOT prefixed with VITE_ so it never reaches the client bundle.
#
# In production this is set instead as a Cloudflare Pages runtime secret named
# GITHUB_TOKEN (Settings -> Variables & Secrets) — never committed.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Cloudflare API access for the Site Health / provisioning diagnostics — used ONLY
# by the dev Cloudflare proxy in vite.config.ts (server-side); like GITHUB_TOKEN
# these are NOT prefixed with VITE_ so they never reach the client bundle. In
# production set the same three as Cloudflare Pages runtime secrets.
#
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN: an Account-scoped token with the minimal permissions
#   Workers KV Storage:Edit, D1:Edit, Workers R2 Storage:Edit, Cloudflare Pages:Edit
#   (nothing else — it can only reach the storage/Pages endpoints on the allowlist).
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID: the account the CMS provisions into (kept server-side; the
#   client sends the `self` placeholder and the proxy substitutes this).
# PAGES_PROJECT: this Pages project's name (the allowlist pins it).
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
PAGES_PROJECT=
